✨️ Disappointingly COOL✨ @typebeautyinc

I really wanted to love this Foundation😭 . An Indian brand is finally making deep foundation shades? That’s a big yessssssssssss 🦋 

I bought their @typebeautyinc get Even foundation samples in the shades - 

375 Cocoa ( which is the last deep shade) ( cool undertone) 
370 Java ( Second last deep shade), (cool undertone)
340 Tiramisu ( third last deep shade) ( Neutral to cool undertone) 

And the sample idea is so smart. Instead of spending ₹1499 straight away, we can test small pots first and mix to get closer to our shade. Win-win, right? 🩷 

But even after all the mixing and trying, the shade is too cool-toned. It makes my skin look dull and muddy instead of fresh and alive. It hurts to say, but I’m disappointed 🥲

The formula itself is matte, full coverage, and strong. Everything my oily skin needs, no problem there. But not for my melanin... and real inclusivity isn’t just about adding the darkest dark right?... The huge jump between cocoa and Java says a lot... We also need those in-between brown, cocoa, and caramel shades, too, with the right undertone.

So yeah, love the idea. But I still couldn’t find my shade. Hoping for more shades that truly see all of us 🌻

Thank you @globalbeautyfinds for asking to try their foundation 🩷... it was a good experience 

Does the Indian beauty Market really overlook the melanin? 

#askandyoushallreceive
